# Customer Who Visited but Did Not Make Any Transactions

## Problem Type
LEFT JOIN + NULL

## What I Learned

- LEFT JOIN keeps all visits.
- Visits without transactions have NULL values.
- Filtered unmatched rows using IS NULL.
- Used GROUP BY to count visits for each customer.

## Pattern

Need records that do not have a matching record.

Use:
LEFT JOIN
WHERE joined_table.column IS NULL

## Difficulty

Easy

##Solution

SELECT 
    v.customer_id, 
    COUNT(v.visit_id) AS count_no_trans
FROM Visits v
LEFT JOIN Transactions t ON v.visit_id = t.visit_id
WHERE t.transaction_id IS NULL
GROUP BY v.customer_id;
